    "title": "LESSON 42: LASSEN CONSTRUCTIONS",
    "header_color": "cyan",
    "pages": [
      {
        "page": 1,
        "total_pages": 1,
        "content": [
          "LASSEN has three main uses:",
          "",
          "1. PERMISSION (let/allow):",
          "Lass mich gehen! (Let me go!)",
          "Ich lasse dich nicht allein. (I won't leave you)",
          "",
          "2. CAUSATIVE (have something done):",
          "Ich lasse das Auto reparieren.",
          "(I'm having the car repaired)",
          "Ich lasse mir die Haare schneiden.",
          "(I'm having my hair cut)",
          "",
          "3. REFLEXIVE (get/have done to oneself):",
          "sich scheiden lassen (get divorced)",
          "sich untersuchen lassen (get examined)",
          "",
          "COMPOUND: entlassen = to fire/dismiss",
          "Er wurde entlassen. (He was fired)",
          "",
          "PERFECT TENSE: lassen stays as infinitive!",
          "Ich habe es reparieren lassen. (not gelassen)"
        ],
        "pronunciation": "Lektion 42"
      }
    ]
  },
